'''伊芙·恩斯勒'''（{{lang-en|Eve Ensler}}，{{bd|1953年|5月25日|catIdx=E}}）是一位美国[[剧作家|剧作家]]，[[表演艺术|表演艺术家]]，[[女性主义者|女性主义者]]和社会活动家，最出名的作品是戏剧《[[阴道独白|阴道独白]]》。<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/10/magazine/eve-ensler-wants-to-save-the-world.html The New York Times] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/10/magazine/eve-ensler-wants-to-save-the-world.html |date=20201018004602 }} 2002/02/10</ref><ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2001/12/09/nyregion/theater-melding-drama-with-politics.html?src=pm The New York Times] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2001/12/09/nyregion/theater-melding-drama-with-politics.html?src=pm |date=20160306113017 }} 2001/12/09</ref><ref name="NYT-2011-12-03">[http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2011/12/02/opinion/magazine-global-agenda-big-question.html Politics, Power and Passion] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2011/12/02/opinion/magazine-global-agenda-big-question.html |date=20170624033013 }}, [[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]], December 2, 2011. Please see the fifth segment by Eve Ensler.</ref>該劇在2006年被《[[纽约时报|紐約時報]]》戲劇評論家{{tsl|en|Charles Isherwood|查爾斯·伊舍伍}}評為「過去十年有重大影響的政治劇場之一」。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/03/theater/03ishe.html|title=The Culture Project and Plays That Make a Difference|author=|last=Isherwood|first=Charles|date=2006-09-03|work=|newspaper=The New York Times|accessdate=2018-03-24|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2019-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510141923/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/09/03/theater/03ishe.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

恩斯勒創立了非營利的「{{tsl|en|V-Day (movement)|V-Day}}」運動，旨在募款並倡議終止對女性暴力，也因此在2011年，恩斯勒於第65屆[[托尼獎|東尼獎]]中獲得「{{tsl|en|Isabelle Stevenson Award|伊莎貝爾·史蒂芬森獎}}」，該獎項表揚在戲劇界中，對於志願、社會服務、慈善等方面做出貢獻的個人。

== 个人生活 ==
恩斯勒出生于纽约市，是一个家庭主妇和食品行业高管的女儿，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=Dhb_CgBFvigC&pg=PA202&dq=Chris+Arthur+Ensler&hl=en&sa=X&ei=4pMxUf6pAYr6qwHnh4HQCw&ved=0CCMQ6AEwAA |title=Insecure at Last: A Political Memoir - Eve Ensler - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.ca |date= |accessdate=2013-05-16 |archive-date=2013-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016085234/http://books.google.ca/books?id=Dhb_CgBFvigC&pg=PA202&dq=Chris+Arthur+Ensler&hl=en&sa=X&ei=4pMxUf6pAYr6qwHnh4HQCw&ved=0CCMQ6AEwAA |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Plummer |first=William |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20133629,00.html |title=V for Victory - Real People Stories, Eve Ensler |publisher=People.com |date= |accessdate=2013-05-16 |archive-date=2016-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415013218/http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20133629,00.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>在家裡的三個小孩中排行第二。她的父亲是犹太人，母亲有基督教背景。<ref name="pfefferman">[http://www.jewishjournal.com/articles/item/navel_gazing_with_eve_ensler_20051209/ Jewish Journal]</ref>

她在2007年出版的书中描述了自己5到10岁时被作为食品公司CEO的父亲强奸和毒打的经历。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenation.com/article/171127/eve-ensler-rising# |title=Eve Ensler Rising |publisher=The Nation |date=2012-11-07 |accessdate=2013-05-16 |archive-date=2015-06-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150603233545/http://www.thenation.com/article/171127/eve-ensler-rising |dead-url=no }}</ref>她說：「我非常傷心、非常憤怒、非常叛逆。我的毛髮骯髒，我不適合任何地方。」<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/archive/v-for-victory-vol-55-no-6/|title=V for Victory – Real People Stories, Eve Ensler|author=WILLIAM PLUMMER|date=|work=|newspaper=PEOPLE.com|accessdate=2018-03-24|language=en|archive-date=2017-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809090236/http://people.com/archive/v-for-victory-vol-55-no-6/|dead-url=no}}</ref>她1975年毕业于[[佛蒙特州|佛蒙特州]]的[[米德尔伯里学院|米德尔伯里学院]]，畢業後開始依賴藥物與酒精。<ref name=":0" />1979年9月17日她嫁给了34歲的[[調酒師|調酒師]]理查‧麥狄蒙（英語：Richard McDermott），丈夫成功地說服恩斯勒接受成癮治療計畫<ref name=":0" />。恩斯勒與家人之間的關係變得緊密，恩斯勒自述這讓她學到「怎麼成為一個有愛的人。」<ref name=":0" />

恩斯勒是演员[[迪倫·麥狄蒙|迪倫·麥狄蒙]]（英語：Dylan McDermott）的养母，当时她23岁，麥狄蒙15岁，迪倫‧麥狄蒙是父親理查與第一任妻子生下的兒子，<ref>McDermott, Shiva Rose. "V-Day Activist Spotlights: Shiva Rose McDermott" [http://www.vday.org/meet-vday/activist-spotlights/shiva-rose-mcdermott Vday.org] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090603231929/http://www.vday.org/meet-vday/activist-spotlights/shiva-rose-mcdermott |date=2009-06-03 }} Retrieved 2009-10-26</ref>迪倫的原名是馬克（英語：Mark McDermott），在恩斯勒的一次流產之後，馬克才將名字改為恩斯勒為未生下的胎兒準備好的名字「迪倫」。<ref name=":0" />恩斯勒也鼓勵迪倫追求演藝事業。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.today.com/news/dylan-mcdermott-path-rediscovery-wbna16932594|title=Dylan McDermott is on a path of rediscovery|newspaper=TODAY.com|accessdate=2018-03-24|language=en-US|archive-date=2018-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702093201/https://www.today.com/news/dylan-mcdermott-path-rediscovery-wbna16932594|dead-url=no}}</ref>

10年后，恩斯勒與丈夫在1988年離婚，恩斯勒認為自己需要獨立與自由。根據《[[雪梨晨鋒報|雪梨晨鋒報]]》的一篇文章指出，「在她的婚姻結束以後，她與藝術家兼心理學家Ariel Orr Jordan有一段很長的關係，但她仍是單身，這似乎符合她流浪的生活風格──她在紐約與巴黎有房子，但她經常旅遊。」<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/interview--eve-ensler-20120112-1pvvm.html|title=Interview: Eve Ensler|accessdate=2018-03-24|date=2012-01-13|last=SANER|first=By EMINE|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127021116/https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/interview--eve-ensler-20120112-1pvvm.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2010年6月12日恩斯勒在《卫报》写了一篇文章，其中提到她正在接受子宫癌的治疗。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2010/jun/12/cancer-atrocities-congo-violence |title=Guardian.co.uk |access-date=2013-07-18 |archive-date=2011-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110121070245/http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2010/jun/12/cancer-atrocities-congo-violence |dead-url=no }}</ref>恩斯勒也在她的回憶錄''In the Body of the World''中寫下她與癌症的故事。<ref>{{Cite book|title=In the Body of the World|last=|first=|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>

== 《阴道独白》 ==
{{main|阴道独白}}
《[[阴道独白|阴道独白]]》写于1996年。首演在[[格林尼治村|格林尼治村]]，《阴道独白》已被翻译成48种语言，并在超过140个国家和地区演出。在剧中出演的名人包括：[[珍·芳達|珍·芳達]]，[[琥碧·戈柏|琥碧·戈柏]]，[[伊迪娜·门泽尔|伊迪娜·门泽尔]]，[[格伦·克洛斯|格伦·克洛斯]]，[[蘇珊·莎蘭登|蘇珊·莎蘭登]]，[[辛蒂·羅波|辛蒂·羅波]]，[[吳珊卓|吳珊卓]]和[[奧花·雲費|奧花·雲費]]。

恩斯勒於1996年獲得{{tsl|en|Obie Award|奧比獎}}最佳新劇獎，並因劇本創作於1999年獲得{{tsl|en|Guggenheim Fellowship|古根漢獎}}。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1999/10/04/theater/theater-review-a-body-part-returns-as-the-leading-lady.html|title=THEATER REVIEW; A Body Part Returns As the Leading Lady|last=Gates|first=Anita|date=1999-10-04|newspaper=The New York Times|accessdate=2018-03-24|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2019-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629120256/https://www.nytimes.com/1999/10/04/theater/theater-review-a-body-part-returns-as-the-leading-lady.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/legit/reviews/in-the-body-of-the-world-review-eve-ensler-1202689740/|title=Off Broadway Review: Eve Ensler’s ‘In The Body of the World’|last=Rizzo|first=Frank|date=2018-02-07|newspaper=Variety|accessdate=2018-03-24|language=en-US|archive-date=2018-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623032832/https://variety.com/2018/legit/reviews/in-the-body-of-the-world-review-eve-ensler-1202689740/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

